This paper deals with the security of Bitcoin against routing attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of inter-domain routing policies (BGP) and programmable network hardware, which are related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.Distributed). The paper also presents a scalable and efficient system, which is related to system design and implementation (cs.SI) and distributed systems (cs.DC).
